<section class="section-white">
  <div class="container" style="max-width:820px">
    <h2 style="font-family:var(--font-display);font-size:clamp(1.7rem,3vw,2.4rem);font-weight:700;color:var(--ink-2);line-height:1.2;margin:38px 0 16px">4 Days + 2 Nights Northern Circuit Tanzania Safari</h2>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">A Short Escape Into Africa's Wild Heart</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">Starting From USD 2654 Per Person *</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">Rates vary depending on season, accommodation type, and group size.</p>
    <h2 style="font-family:var(--font-display);font-size:clamp(1.7rem,3vw,2.4rem);font-weight:700;color:var(--ink-2);line-height:1.2;margin:38px 0 16px">Safari Overview</h2>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">This 4-day Northern Circuit safari is a carefully designed journey through Tanzania's most iconic wildlife destinations. From the elephant-rich landscapes of Tarangire to the endless plains of the Serengeti and the breathtaking Ngorongoro Crater, this experience delivers pure wilderness, dramatic scenery, and unforgettable game viewing in a short but powerful adventure.</p>
    <h2 style="font-family:var(--font-display);font-size:clamp(1.7rem,3vw,2.4rem);font-weight:700;color:var(--ink-2);line-height:1.2;margin:38px 0 16px">Day 1: Arrival in Tanzania - Welcome to Arusha</h2>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">Your journey begins the moment you land at Kilimanjaro International Airport (JRO), where your professional safari guide warmly welcomes you to Tanzania. You will then be transferred to your lodge in Arusha, a peaceful safari town set beneath Mount Meru.</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">This is a day to relax, recover from your journey, and slowly transition into the rhythm of Africa. Depending on arrival time, you may enjoy a quiet evening at the lodge surrounded by nature and fresh mountain air.</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">Accommodation: River Trees In</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">Board Basis: HB</p>
    <h2 style="font-family:var(--font-display);font-size:clamp(1.7rem,3vw,2.4rem);font-weight:700;color:var(--ink-2);line-height:1.2;margin:38px 0 16px">Day 2: Tarangire National Park - Land of Giants</h2>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">After breakfast, depart for Tarangire National Park, a hidden gem famous for its massive elephant herds and ancient baobab trees that dominate the landscape.</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">Enjoy a full-day game drive through rolling savannahs and seasonal river valleys where wildlife gathers in abundance. Expect encounters with elephants, lions, giraffes, zebras, wildebeest, buffaloes, and rich birdlife.</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">The Tarangire River becomes the lifeline of the park, attracting animals from far and wide, creating excellent game-viewing opportunities throughout the day.</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">As the sun sets over the golden horizon, proceed to your lodge for dinner and overnight.</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">Accommodation: Manyara Best View Lodge</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">Board Basis: FB</p>
    <h2 style="font-family:var(--font-display);font-size:clamp(1.7rem,3vw,2.4rem);font-weight:700;color:var(--ink-2);line-height:1.2;margin:38px 0 16px">Day 3: Serengeti National Park - Into the Endless Plains</h2>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">Today you travel through the scenic Ngorongoro Highlands en route to the world-famous Serengeti National Park. Along the way, enjoy breathtaking views of volcanic landscapes, Maasai villages, and open wilderness.</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">Upon entering the Serengeti, the land transforms into endless golden plains stretching beyond the horizon. Begin your first game drive as you explore one of the most celebrated wildlife ecosystems on Earth.</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">This is predator country-lions, cheetahs, and leopards roam freely while large herds of herbivores graze across the plains.</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">Accommodation: Baobab Central Serengeti</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">Board Basis: FB</p>
    <h2 style="font-family:var(--font-display);font-size:clamp(1.7rem,3vw,2.4rem);font-weight:700;color:var(--ink-2);line-height:1.2;margin:38px 0 16px">Day 4: Full Day Serengeti Experience - The Wild Theatre</h2>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">Spend the entire day exploring the vast Serengeti ecosystem. Early morning and afternoon game drives offer the best chances to witness active wildlife behavior, from hunting predators to grazing herds.</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">Depending on the season, you may witness parts of the Great Migration, where thousands of wildebeest and zebras move across the plains in search of fresh grazing land.</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">Enjoy a picnic lunch in the wilderness, surrounded by nature and silence broken only by distant animal calls.</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">Optional hot-air balloon safari can be arranged for a breathtaking sunrise experience above the savannah.</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">Accommodation: Baobab Tented Lodge</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">Board Basis: FB</p>
    <h2 style="font-family:var(--font-display);font-size:clamp(1.7rem,3vw,2.4rem);font-weight:700;color:var(--ink-2);line-height:1.2;margin:38px 0 16px">Day 5: Ngorongoro Crater - Africa's Natural Wonder</h2>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">After an early breakfast and final Serengeti game drive, depart for the Ngorongoro Conservation Area.</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">Descend 600 meters into the Ngorongoro Crater, a UNESCO World Heritage Site and one of the most wildlife-dense areas in Africa. The crater floor offers a unique ecosystem where lions, elephants, buffaloes, hippos, hyenas, and the rare black rhino can all be seen in one place.</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">Enjoy a scenic picnic lunch inside the crater while surrounded by dramatic landscapes and abundant wildlife.</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">Later in the afternoon, ascend the crater rim and continue to your lodge.</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">Accommodation: Bougainvillea Lodge</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">Board Basis: FB</p>
    <h2 style="font-family:var(--font-display);font-size:clamp(1.7rem,3vw,2.4rem);font-weight:700;color:var(--ink-2);line-height:1.2;margin:38px 0 16px">Day 6: Departure - Gentle Goodbye</h2>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">Enjoy a relaxed breakfast at your lodge with views of the Ngorongoro Highlands.</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">Afterward, drive back to Arusha where you may have time for souvenir shopping or a short city experience depending on your flight schedule. Later, transfer to Kilimanjaro International Airport for your departure.</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">As your safari ends, you leave with unforgettable memories of Tanzania's wildlife, landscapes, and warm hospitality.</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">Board Basis: BB</p>
  </div>
</section>

